text: Gymnothorax goldsboroughi Jordan & Evermann The elegant moray (Gymnothorax elegans), or Goldsborough's moray eel,Common names for Gymnothorax elegans at www.fishbase.org. is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian Oceans.Gymnothorax elegans at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Bliss in 1883. == References == elegans Category:Fish described in 1883
